    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset represents a univariate compositional breakdown of Earth's water distribution across 12 subcategories. Original NASA hydrological data (3 main categories) was expanded through synthetic decomposition using hydrological studies' typical distribution patterns, maintaining category sum constraints (Saltwater: \u221185+8+4=97%, Ice: \u22111.5+0.4+0.1=2%, Freshwater: \u22110.6+0.3+0.05+0.03+0.02+0.01=1.01% accounting for rounding). The nested pie visualization employs Tufte's data-ink ratio by eliminating gridlines while using: 1) Monochromatic sequential coloring for category groups (saltwater=light blues, ice=medium blues, freshwater=dark blues), 2) Cairo's preattentive texture principles through varied segment angles, and 3) Proximity grouping in the legend. Interactive tooltips with D3-style formatting (+.2f precision) reveal exact percentages, while the exploded groundwater segment highlights the most accessible freshwater source. Statistical validity is maintained through proportional constraints (\u03bc_salt=97% \u00b1 \u03c3=0.5% via synthetic decomposition)."
